l intervention in the debates which surround Malle’s work.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture producers and directorszFrance. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aLe Souffle au cœur.  aLouis Malle.  aambiguous rhetorical strategies.  acultural right-wing.  alibertarian left.  anew political questioning.  apost-war international cinema.  apublic controversy.  ayouthful bravado.1 aFrey, Hugo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614161340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526141613423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526141613/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles